               <head>Sihr-i halal</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">1 copy of Siḥr-i ḥalāl by Ahlī Shīrāzī, Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf, 1454-1535 or 1536</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Uk_Or_15563-item1" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100084">
                     <author change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard" key="ark:/81055/vdc_100164657193.0x000001 viaf_36817419">Ahlī Shīrāzī, Muḥammad ibn Yūsuf, 1454-1535 or 1536</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa" type="supplied" key="viaf_36817419">اهلي شيرازي، محمد بن يوسف</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7025">Siḥr-i ḥalāl</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7025">سحر حلال</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>A mas̲navī poem on the love-story of Prince Jam and Princess Gul, with a preface in prose, by Muḥammad Ahlī Shīrāzī (d. 942/1535-6).</p>
                        <p>This poem has several remarkable artistic features: it has two different rhymes and scans in two metres; and each bayt contains a tajnīs.</p>
                        <p>Other contents: owner’s inscription with title and price, f. 1v.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
